text: François Vannson in Saint-Dié-des-Vosges, 2015 François Vannson (born October 20, 1962 in Épinal) was a member of the National Assembly of France. He represented the Vosges department from 1993 to 2017 as a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:People from Épinal Category:Rally for the Republic politicians Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:The Popular Right Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
